<div class="cell-sm-6">
    <div class="range">
        <div class="cell-xs-24 cell-md-12" style="margin-bottom:35px;">
            <article class="icon-box-vertical">
                <img src="\assets\images\claremont-eap-logo.png" />
                <p>The Plan’s Employee Assistance Program and Chemical Dependency Treatment services is through Claremont EAP.  This program is effective January 1, 2015 and is available to all active Health Fund members and their eligible dependents.  This includes both Kaiser and Indemnity Plan members and dependents.</br></br>Because personal concerns can have a big impact on work performance and overall wellbeing, we can all use extra support at some point in our lives. Claremont EAP can help resolve personal issues before they become more serious and difficult to manage.  You and your family members can receive professional, confidential counseling at no cost.  The EAP also provides access to Chemical Dependency Treatment and other resources that can help you address virtually any family/health need.</br></br><b>To access services, call (800) 834-3773.</b> A Claremont counselor will help you develop an action plan and refer you to the resources most appropriate for your needs.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
        <div class="cell-xs-24 cell-md-12" style="margin-bottom:35px;">
            <article class="icon-box-vertical">
                <h4 class="icon-box-header" style="color:#000;">Chemical Dependency Case Management Services</h4>
                <p>Claremont will manage Chemical Dependency Treatment Services available through your health plan.  The Trustees feel Claremont will be able to offer timely assistance to eligible Fund participants in assessing potential problems and providing access to effective and appropriate services.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
